ng":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"**Describe the bug**\nFrom version 3.25.0, it seems that method `usingRecursiveFieldByFieldElementComparatorOnFields` on `AbstractIterableAssert` returns an error if one of the fields don't exist. The problem is that I have polymorphic objects.\n\n* assertj core version: 3.25.0\n* java version: 21\n* test framework version: junit 5.11.4\n* os (if relevant): \n\n**Test case reproducing the bug**\n\nAdd a test case showing the bug that we can run\n\n```java\n\n@Data\n@SuperBuilder\npublic abstract sealed class AppliedExemptionResponse permits AppliedTotalExemptionResponse, AppliedPartialExemptionResponse {\n\tString exemptionCode;\n\tString description;\n\tString chargeItemCode;\n\tString description;\n}\n\n@Value\n@SuperBuilder\npublic class AppliedTotalExemptionResponse extends AppliedExemptionResponse {\n}\n\n@Value\n@SuperBuilder\npublic class AppliedPartialExemptionResponse extends AppliedExemptionResponse {\n\tBigDecimal value;\n\tString type;\n\tboolean replacement;\n}\n\npublic class MyTest {\n\n\t@Test\n\tvoid test() {\n\n\t\tfinal List<AppliedExemptionResponse> appliedExemptions = List.of(\n\t\t\t\tAppliedTotalExemptionResponse.builder().exemptionCode( \"E1\" ).build(),\n\t\t\t\tAppliedPartialExemptionResponse.builder().value( BigDecimal.ZERO ).build()\n\t\t);\n\t\tfinal List<AppliedExemptionResponse> expectedAppliedExemptions = List.of(\n\t\t\t\tAppliedTotalExemptionResponse.builder().exemptionCode( \"E1\" ).build(),\n\t\t\t\tAppliedPartialExemptionResponse.builder().value( BigDecimal.ZERO ).build()\n\t\t);\n\n\t\tassertThat( appliedExemptions )\n\t\t\t\t.usingRecursiveFieldByFieldElementComparatorOnFields( \"exemptionCode\", \"chargeItemCode\", \"description\", \"value\" )\n\t\t\t\t.containsExactlyInAnyOrderElementsOf( expectedAppliedExemptions );\n\t}\n}\n```\n\nThe test fails with the following error:\n\n`java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: The following fields don't exist: {value}`\n\nHow can I fix the problem?\n","clos